race.comment: CERTIFIED COPY (9) showed sharp early speed at Ballina last start and fought on bravely to finish a close second. He looks to be peaking now and only needs to hold that level to break through. AUNTY RENE (11) wasn't disgraced when resuming in town and should strip fitter for that effort. With a kinder draw here, she finds a suitable race to end a long run of outs. HOLLYWOOD EPIC (6) is in outstanding form, chasing a hat-trick of wins, and gets in well again with the claim. He draws favourably and must be taken very seriously. MOUNT FUJI (3) produced a dominant win here last time, showing a sharp turn of foot. This is tougher and the draw makes life harder, but he's clearly in good order. WRITTEN FAME (1) disappointed at short odds last start but is better than that run suggests. Has the pace to offset the draw and is worth another chance.
